        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How do you develop probabilistic thinking?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Probabilistic thinking develops through three practices: tracking your predictions with explicit probability estimates and scoring accuracy afterward (calibration training), consulting base rates before relying on specific case information, and learning to assign numerical probabilities to beliefs rather than categorical labels. Keeping a decision journal and reviewing outcomes builds the feedback loop essential for calibration."
        }
      },
